00:35:44.510 --> 00:35:48.890
MINGMING YANG: The
unblinded two-photon results

00:35:48.890 --> 00:35:52.600
giving the first convincing
evidence of the existence

00:35:52.600 --> 00:35:55.600
of a new particle.

00:35:55.600 --> 00:36:00.060
Night of that day, CERN
building two, fourth floor.

00:36:00.060 --> 00:36:06.190
We just experienced a historic
moment, said Christoph.

00:36:06.190 --> 00:36:07.950
Yes, we did.

00:36:07.950 --> 00:36:11.340
Not just in the
history of science.

00:36:11.340 --> 00:36:14.580
I did not speak out.

00:36:14.580 --> 00:36:19.240
What else do I still
remember during that day?

00:36:19.240 --> 00:36:23.150
This smiles from the
bottom of everyone's heart.

00:36:23.150 --> 00:36:25.760
Our final results
continue showing

00:36:25.760 --> 00:36:30.770
an excess around 125
GeV, which, combined

00:36:30.770 --> 00:36:35.900
with all the other
Higgs channels,

00:36:35.900 --> 00:36:42.500
gave the significance of
excess reach five sigma,

00:36:42.500 --> 00:36:46.590
the conventional criteria
to claim the discovery

00:36:46.590 --> 00:36:48.300
of a new particle.

00:36:48.300 --> 00:36:51.520
In the same time,
a similar excess

00:36:51.520 --> 00:36:55.510
was also observed from
the Atlas experiment.

00:36:55.510 --> 00:36:59.720
On July 4, 2012,
both experiments

00:36:59.720 --> 00:37:03.450
announced the discovery
of a new particle at CERN

00:37:03.450 --> 00:37:07.230
in a joint seminar with
the 36th International

00:37:07.230 --> 00:37:10.070
Conference of
High-Energy Physics, held

00:37:10.070 --> 00:37:11.495
at Melbourne, Australia.

00:37:14.330 --> 00:37:19.120
And you can see our
final plots showing

00:37:19.120 --> 00:37:25.170
both the signal and the
significance of the excess.

00:37:25.170 --> 00:37:27.710
And you can also
see the pictures

00:37:27.710 --> 00:37:30.810
at the bottom showing the
situation in the auditorium

00:37:30.810 --> 00:37:32.150
at CERN on that day.

00:37:35.000 --> 00:37:38.580
Fabian was taking a night
shift, and he didn't make it

00:37:38.580 --> 00:37:44.020
to the auditorium, and we
didn't stop working on that day.

00:37:44.020 --> 00:37:49.520
And we did not have too
much time to celebrate, just

00:37:49.520 --> 00:37:53.790
except for taking a
couple of beers together.

00:37:53.790 --> 00:37:58.770
The world started swirling
while we kept working.

00:37:58.770 --> 00:38:03.220
The center of a storm
was always quiet.

00:38:03.220 --> 00:38:08.070
We didn't get any award,
but we have already

00:38:08.070 --> 00:38:12.410
get the best award
from nature itself.

00:38:12.410 --> 00:38:15.572
After discovery, we
continued to verify

00:38:15.572 --> 00:38:17.030
the observation of
the new particle

00:38:17.030 --> 00:38:19.980
and measure its properties
and check its compatibility

00:38:19.980 --> 00:38:22.100
with the Higgs boson.

00:38:22.100 --> 00:38:28.560
On June 15, 2015, I
submitted my PhD thesis,

00:38:28.560 --> 00:38:31.240
which concluded the journey
that I had experienced

00:38:31.240 --> 00:38:35.180
with my teammates and colleagues
with the stand-alone discovery

00:38:35.180 --> 00:38:38.950
of the Higgs boson through
the two-photon channel.

00:38:38.950 --> 00:38:41.670
And I have been
traveling since then,

00:38:41.670 --> 00:38:45.910
and writing this
story, "The Discovery."

00:38:45.910 --> 00:38:52.700
I want to share you the
end part of this story.

00:38:52.700 --> 00:38:57.370
This is the end of my story of
searching for the Higgs boson.

00:38:57.370 --> 00:39:02.322
During my travel from my
hometown to edge of Alaska,

00:39:02.322 --> 00:39:04.790
I have encountered
different people on

00:39:04.790 --> 00:39:09.090
the road-- high school
student, bookshop staff,

00:39:09.090 --> 00:39:13.310
elementary school teacher,
businessman, piano technician,

00:39:13.310 --> 00:39:17.910
taxi driver, probation officer,
raspberry farmer, plumber,

00:39:17.910 --> 00:39:23.100
mechanic, air flight controller,
coffee shop worker, lawyer,

00:39:23.100 --> 00:39:28.060
writer, art gallery host,
firefighter, painter, drummer,

00:39:28.060 --> 00:39:32.451
aerial silk dancer, gold
miner, single-handed sailor,

00:39:32.451 --> 00:39:34.610
fisherman.

00:39:34.610 --> 00:39:38.450
It is my pleasure to share with
them the Higgs search story

00:39:38.450 --> 00:39:42.630
and listen to their stories
back, and find how similar

00:39:42.630 --> 00:39:46.760
the story of fisherman searching
for the salmon at Bering Sea

00:39:46.760 --> 00:39:52.524
to our story of search for the
Higgs boson among the data sea.

00:39:52.524 --> 00:39:57.070
The hardship, the
friendship, the passion,

00:39:57.070 --> 00:39:59.640
and the feeling of
the power and beauty

00:39:59.640 --> 00:40:03.750
of nature-- after
all, human activities

00:40:03.750 --> 00:40:06.750
share the same common ground.

00:40:06.750 --> 00:40:10.290
And I'm glad to receive
a small toy occasionally,

00:40:10.290 --> 00:40:15.700
in a red Alaska crab
from 9-year-old Jenna.

00:40:15.700 --> 00:40:18.980
Sometimes I'm asked,
what is the significance

00:40:18.980 --> 00:40:23.490
of searching for the Higgs
boson to me and to human beings?

00:40:23.490 --> 00:40:27.330
I have been thinking about
these questions myself

00:40:27.330 --> 00:40:31.380
when walking on the road between
CERN and Saint-Genis-Pouilly,

00:40:31.380 --> 00:40:36.330
when writing my thesis, and
when s sitting on the train.

00:40:36.330 --> 00:40:40.210
I still remember a
conversation with Christoph

00:40:40.210 --> 00:40:45.180
at CERN, building 32,
fourth floor, in 2011.

00:40:45.180 --> 00:40:50.170
I told him that no matter
whether we make a discovery

00:40:50.170 --> 00:40:54.980
or not, and whether I
would get a PhD or not,

00:40:54.980 --> 00:40:58.550
I would never regret
coming and working here.

00:40:58.550 --> 00:41:00.980
This is my choice of life.

00:41:00.980 --> 00:41:04.040
And I want to say the same now.

00:41:04.040 --> 00:41:07.150
It is thrilling to have
been deeply involved

00:41:07.150 --> 00:41:11.290
with the milestone of the
discovery of the Higgs boson.

00:41:11.290 --> 00:41:15.180
But having worked
together with these people

00:41:15.180 --> 00:41:19.080
in that space at that time
itself is thrilling no

00:41:19.080 --> 00:41:21.520
matter the outcome.

00:41:21.520 --> 00:41:25.900
To me, connecting to the
generations of physicists,

00:41:25.900 --> 00:41:30.160
pursuing a common goal,
witnessing and devoting myself

00:41:30.160 --> 00:41:34.420
for the monumental effort of
human beings, along with all

00:41:34.420 --> 00:41:37.790
the colleagues,
discovering and interacting

00:41:37.790 --> 00:41:40.670
with all the beautiful
minds and hearts,

00:41:40.670 --> 00:41:45.690
continuously discovering myself
and feeling the deep harmony

00:41:45.690 --> 00:41:48.520
with nature, are the
most precious parts

00:41:48.520 --> 00:41:52.000
of the journey searching
for the Higgs boson.

00:41:52.000 --> 00:41:56.260
All my work is not for a PhD,
and even not for the Higgs

00:41:56.260 --> 00:42:00.290
discovery, but for life itself.

00:42:00.290 --> 00:42:02.940
And it has already been
finished long before,

00:42:02.940 --> 00:42:06.500
and has been contained
in all the moments.

00:42:06.500 --> 00:42:08.755
My main motivation
to write a thesis

00:42:08.755 --> 00:42:13.680
is to use the opportunity
to tell these people I have

00:42:13.680 --> 00:42:17.370
worked with that I love them.

00:42:17.370 --> 00:42:20.770
The analysis for the Higgs
search could be repeated,

00:42:20.770 --> 00:42:24.180
but those moments and the
stories of these people

00:42:24.180 --> 00:42:26.270
are not replaceable.

00:42:26.270 --> 00:42:29.100
Many of the stories
are very lovely.

00:42:29.100 --> 00:42:32.360
They probably will
never be stated.

00:42:32.360 --> 00:42:37.020
But they have been detected
and started in my heart,

00:42:37.020 --> 00:42:41.640
and probably only the people who
have experienced and witnessed

00:42:41.640 --> 00:42:47.220
these stories would feel
the deepest resonance.

00:42:47.220 --> 00:42:49.960
The [INAUDIBLE] journey
has been wonderful,

00:42:49.960 --> 00:42:52.350
especially because
I have shared it

00:42:52.350 --> 00:42:56.060
with some people who,
whenever I think of them,

00:42:56.060 --> 00:42:58.882
bring hot tears to my eyes.

00:42:58.882 --> 00:43:02.750
I would choose the same
way to spend my 20s again

00:43:02.750 --> 00:43:07.200
and again, If i were given the
infinite chance to step back,

00:43:07.200 --> 00:43:10.090
and infinite ways to choose.

00:43:10.090 --> 00:43:12.640
I will continue to
discover that future

00:43:12.640 --> 00:43:17.090
from all the uncertainties,
following the sky above me

00:43:17.090 --> 00:43:19.750
and the road within my heart.

00:43:19.750 --> 00:43:24.500
I hope this road will lead
to the liberation of the soul

00:43:24.500 --> 00:43:27.970
and enrichment of the
spirit of a human being

00:43:27.970 --> 00:43:31.590
and of human beings, as what
this Higgs search journey

00:43:31.590 --> 00:43:35.160
should ultimately lead to.

00:43:35.160 --> 00:43:41.080
The train keeps moving into
vast space at the front of time.

00:43:41.080 --> 00:43:43.800
What is the ultimate reality?

00:43:43.800 --> 00:43:46.230
Is the observed
particle the ripple

00:43:46.230 --> 00:43:48.710
of the field slowing
down the particles

00:43:48.710 --> 00:43:51.900
with mass such that
they could get together

00:43:51.900 --> 00:43:54.520
to form the structures
in the universe,

00:43:54.520 --> 00:43:58.260
including ourselves, as
described by the standard model

00:43:58.260 --> 00:44:00.480
of particle physics?

00:44:00.480 --> 00:44:04.050
Our understanding always
progresses with time,

00:44:04.050 --> 00:44:06.720
and the future will unblind.

00:44:06.720 --> 00:44:10.560
What is sure for the moment,
search for the Higgs boson

00:44:10.560 --> 00:44:14.890
does bring us together to
experience a series of events

00:44:14.890 --> 00:44:19.870
in that space and time,
becoming a monumental part

00:44:19.870 --> 00:44:23.730
of our-- a fundamental
part of existence

00:44:23.730 --> 00:44:27.460
and a monumental part
of human history.

00:44:27.460 --> 00:44:29.320
All the information
we have obtained

00:44:29.320 --> 00:44:31.780
from the proton-proton
collisions at the Large Hadron

00:44:31.780 --> 00:44:35.540
Collider, along with all
the efforts of generations

00:44:35.540 --> 00:44:39.150
of physicists and engineers
over the world, all

00:44:39.150 --> 00:44:43.770
the sleepless nights, all
the memorable moments, all

00:44:43.770 --> 00:44:47.780
the collisions among ourselves,
all the beautiful minds

00:44:47.780 --> 00:44:52.290
and hearts, all the
emotions and all the stories

00:44:52.290 --> 00:44:56.530
are folded into the results
sent towards the future,

00:44:56.530 --> 00:45:01.280
passing through layers of time
as pairs of photons passing

00:45:01.280 --> 00:45:04.480
through layers of
nights as what we have

00:45:04.480 --> 00:45:08.540
received from our predecessors.

00:45:08.540 --> 00:45:11.000
And all the
significance is already

00:45:11.000 --> 00:45:13.890
contained in the
human activities that

00:45:13.890 --> 00:45:20.470
connect us with each other,
with nature, and with ourselves.

00:45:20.470 --> 00:45:24.980
At this moment, my
heart has already

00:45:24.980 --> 00:45:30.600
melted into infinite
pairs of protons

00:45:30.600 --> 00:45:37.110
colliding at infinite points
in that space and time,

00:45:37.110 --> 00:45:42.930
producing infinite pairs,
producing infinite number

00:45:42.930 --> 00:45:49.370
of Higgs bosons decaying to
infinite pairs of photons,

00:45:49.370 --> 00:45:53.190
pairing all my infinite
[INAUDIBLE] moments,

00:45:53.190 --> 00:45:57.010
flying towards the future.

00:45:57.010 --> 00:45:59.390
What is eternity?

00:45:59.390 --> 00:46:02.410
Every moment is eternity.

00:46:02.410 --> 00:46:07.130
This story is for you, and for
students and researchers who

00:46:07.130 --> 00:46:09.830
silently devote
all of themselves

00:46:09.830 --> 00:46:12.070
to the search for
the Higgs boson.

00:46:12.070 --> 00:46:14.810
Thank you for listening.

